   "source": [
    "# Introduction to SISO"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from mdof.utilities.printing import *\n",
    "from mdof.utilities.testing import test_method\n",
    "from mdof.utilities.config import Config\n",
    "import mdof\n",
    "from mdof import modal, transform\n",
    "from control import ss, forced_response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Define a SDOF system\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "m  | mass\n",
    "k  | stiffness\n",
    "c  | damping coefficient\n",
    "nt | number of timesteps\n",
    "dt | timestep"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![sdof](./figures/sdof.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "natural period: 1.1471s\n",
      "damping ratio: 0.05\n",
      "['forcing periods: 0.09311283477587824', 'forcing periods: 0.7668115805072326', 'forcing periods: 2.557864343549126', 'forcing periods: 1.018763956959609', 'forcing periods: 1.608661151392673']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# parameters of SDOF system\n",
    "mass = 1       # mass\n",
    "k = 30         # stiffness\n",
    "zeta = 0.05    # damping ratio\n",
    "omega_n = np.sqrt(k/mass)  # natural frequency (rad/s)\n",
    "Tn = 2*np.pi/omega_n  # natural periods (s)\n",
    "c = 2*zeta*mass*omega_n    # damping coefficient\n",
    "print(f\"natural period: {Tn:<3.5}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"damping ratio: {zeta}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# forcing frequencies (rad/s)\n",
    "omega_f = [0.017*omega_n, 0.14*omega_n, 0.467*omega_n, 0.186*omega_n, 0.2937*omega_n]\n",
    "print([f\"forcing periods: {omega}\" for omega in omega_f])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# forcing function (input)\n",
    "nt = 5000       # number of timesteps\n",
    "dt = 0.03       # timestep\n",
    "tf = nt*dt      # final time\n",
    "t = np.arange(start = 0, stop = tf, step = dt)\n",
    "f = np.sum(np.sin([omega*t for omega in omega_f]), axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# displacement response (analytical solution) (output)\n",
    "omega_D = omega_n*np.sqrt(1-zeta**2)\n",
    "y = np.zeros((len(omega_f),nt))\n",
    "for i,omega in enumerate(omega_f):\n",
    "    C3 = (1/k)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C4 = -(2*zeta*omega/omega_n)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C1 = -C4\n",
    "    C2 = (zeta*omega_n*C1-omega*C3)/omega_D\n",
    "    y[i,:] = np.exp(-zeta*omega_n*t)*(C1*np.cos(omega_D*t)+C2*np.sin(omega_D*t)) + C3*np.sin(omega*t) + C4*np.cos(omega*t)\n",
    "y = np.sum(y,axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x300 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot input vs. output\n",
    "plot_io(inputs=f, outputs=y, t=t, title=\"SDOF Displacement Response to Sinusoidal Forcing\")"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "# Set parameters\n",
    "conf = Config()\n",
    "conf.damping = zeta\n",
    "conf.period_band = (0.01,3) # Period band (s)\n",
    "\n",
    "# A place to store models and their predictions\n",
    "transfer_models = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate a transfer function representation of the system\n",
    "transfer_models[\"Fourier Transform\"] = transform.fourier_transfer(inputs=f, outputs=y, step=dt, **conf)\n",
    "transfer_models[\"Power Transform\"] = transform.power_transfer(inputs=f, outputs=y, step=dt, **conf)\n",
    "# transfer_models[\"Response Spectrum\"] = transform.response_transfer(inputs=f, outputs=y, step=dt, pseudo=False, threads=8, periods=(*conf.period_band, 500), **conf)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Determing the fundamental frequency\n",
    "fourier_periods, fourier_amplitudes = modal.spectrum_modes(*transfer_models[\"Fourier Transform\"],height=0.2)\n",
    "power_periods, power_amplitudes = modal.spectrum_modes(*transfer_models[\"Power Transform\"],height=0.2)\n",
    "# response_periods, response_amplitudes = modal.spectrum_modes(*transfer_models[\"Response Spectrum\"],height=0.1)\n",
    "plot_transfer(transfer_models, title=\"Transfer Functions\")\n",
    "color_cycle = plt.rcParams['axes.prop_cycle'].by_key()['color']\n",
    "# plt.vlines([fourier_periods[0], response_periods[0]],ymin=0,ymax=1,linestyles='--',colors=color_cycle[:2])\n",
    "plt.text(fourier_periods[0]+0.05,0.9,r\"$T_{fourier}$ = \"+str(np.round(fourier_periods[0],3)),fontsize=15)\n",
    "plt.text(power_periods[0]+0.05,0.7,r\"$T_{power}$ = \"+str(np.round(power_periods[0],3)),fontsize=15)\n",
    "# plt.text(response_periods[0]+0.05,0.8,r\"$T_{response}$ = \"+str(np.round(response_periods[0],3)),fontsize=15)\n",
    "plt.xlim(conf.period_band);\n",
    "# plt.gcf().set_figwidth(9)\n",
    "# plt.legend();"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "# Generate a state space realization of the system\n",
    "A,B,C,D = mdof.system(inputs=f, outputs=y, r=2)\n",
    "# Obtain natural period and damping ratio from the state space model\n",
    "ss_modes = modal.system_modes((A,B,C,D),dt,outlook=190)\n",
    "print_modes(ss_modes, Tn=Tn, zeta=zeta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Reproduce the response with the state space model\n",
    "y_mdof = forced_response(ss(A,B,C,D,dt), T=t, U=f, squeeze=False, return_x=False).outputs\n",
    "plot_pred(ytrue=y, models=y_mdof, t=t, title=\"System ID Predicted Displacement Response\")"
   ]
